                    h1 "THE CARR HAS NO DRIVER AND THE COOK COOKS NO MORE"
                    small Mystery Surrounds Missing Owner
                    p
                        | The police have raised the trape threat to “Severe,” following the delivery of a mysterious telegram last night: “THE CARR HAS NO DRIVER AND THE COOK COOKS NO MORE.”
                    p
                        | According to a police spokesperson, the anonymous message pertains to an ongoing investigation into the disappearance of team owner Corey Hawk.
                    p
                        | “We fear the worst," the spokesperson said. “Carr and Cook were Caffreine Free’s only hopes following a singularly disastrous draft. Whether Hawk’s disappearance is of his own accord or against his will, we fear these injuries leave him vulnerable to trape.”
                    p
                        | The well-respected owner and perennial contender has acted erratically this season on his way to a 1-3 record, bungling his auction budget, and, in an act of sheer delirium, spending $40 on James White, who was later dropped. 
                    p
                        | Hawk was last seen spending $120 on Tarik Cohen and Kenny Golladay, who have since combined for 23.1 points. 
                    p
                        | We will update this story as more information from the investigation becomes public.
                    h3 Waiver Report
                    p
                        | Owners had a good week on the wire streaming defenses with Bob Evans, Sarah London's Disapproval, and ISC all netting a defense with 6 or more points. Bearly Awake had the top two waiver pickups. His top pick, Wendell Smallwood, finished with 13.9 points but that good news was offset by Sanu, his other top pick, leaving the game early with an injury. All in all, Bearly Awake should be pretty happy with his waiver decisions, especially at the price point of just $15. The most controversial pickup of the week has to be Jameis Winston going to a team that already rostered two QBs. Trashman Industries offered a simple explanation: trash is trash. With 21 QBs currently rostered and Week 5 byes about to begin, one has to wonder how this story will end.
